FuncDef: This command is used to configure the node in FIPS-140-2 mode. Before using this command, the operator must ensure that no current configuration exists in the config file that is not supported in FIPS-140-2 mode. Failing to remove unsupported configuration will result in the node being unable to boot up. The node must be rebooted after executing this command in order for the node to begin operating in FIPS-140-2 mode.
